    "summary": "Working as Collection Specialist you have to be ready to make decisions which impactscustomers, sales, finance and in the end the entire business. For that reason, many different things have to be taken into consideration in order to keep a balanced relationship between the companies.\nOne of my favourite part at this job is to use my creativity to convince customers to pay and to negotiate what is the best for both parties. A happy and grateful customer is priceless.\nI help improving the DSO, ADD, maximizing the incoming cash flow and reducing the risk of bad debt by negotiating with customers.\nI love all challenges and I like to learn every day something new and different. I am very open to new experiences, improvements and \u2018out of the box\u2019 ideas that makes me a better person and a better professional. \nI am very flexible and enjoy working in a team.\nI equally like to work with SAP and Excel and I am open to new systems.\nPlease note my background is in Sales and Management as I have worked in my family\u2019s furniture business for almost 20 years. This is why I am passionate about everything related to negotiation.",
